Module kivakit.interfaces
Package com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.time

Interface LengthOfTime<Duration extends LengthOfTime<Duration>>

All Superinterfaces:
Comparable<LengthOfTime<?>>, DoubleQuantizable, Quantizable, QuantumComparable<LengthOfTime<?>>, Stringable, StringSource, TimeMeasurement
All Known Implementing Classes:
Duration
public interface LengthOfTime<Duration extends LengthOfTime<Duration>> extends QuantumComparable<LengthOfTime<?>>, Comparable<LengthOfTime<?>>, Stringable, TimeMeasurement
Interface to an object having a length of time, measured in nanoseconds.

Measurement

  • TimeMeasurement.nanoseconds()
  • TimeMeasurement.milliseconds()

Conversion

A length of time can be converted to specific time units by calling one of the following methods:

  • TimeMeasurement.asNanoseconds()
  • TimeMeasurement.asMicroseconds()
  • TimeMeasurement.asMilliseconds()
  • TimeMeasurement.asSeconds()
  • TimeMeasurement.asMinutes()
  • TimeMeasurement.asHours()
  • TimeMeasurement.asDays()
  • TimeMeasurement.asWeeks()
  • TimeMeasurement.asYears()
  • asJavaDuration()

Arithmetic

  • plus(LengthOfTime)
  • minus(LengthOfTime)
  • times(double)
  • dividedBy(double)

Comparison

  • compareTo(LengthOfTime)
  • QuantumComparable.isLessThan(Quantizable)
  • QuantumComparable.isLessThanOrEqualTo(Quantizable)
  • QuantumComparable.isGreaterThan(Quantizable)
  • QuantumComparable.isLessThanOrEqualTo(Quantizable)
  • QuantumComparable.isApproximately(Quantizable, Quantizable)
  • Quantizable.isZero()
  • Quantizable.isNonZero()

Operations

  • await(Awaitable)
  • repeat(Callback)
  • sleep()
  • wait(Object)
  • waitThen(Callback)
